# GameHoverDetails: preview vs hover parity

When editing **GameHoverDetails** hover UI or settings preview:

- **`GameHoverDetailsHoverService`** defines the real popup. **`GameHoverDetailsSettingsView`** must stay visually and structurally aligned for titles, glyph chip column, width, block spacing, separators, and panel chrome.
- **Titles** — Game-art keys (`HoverFieldCatalog.IsGameArtImageField`: Icon, Cover Image, Background Image) have **no** title row in the hover (`TryAppendGameArtRow`). The settings preview must not show field titles for those keys when mirroring the hover (`ShowFieldTitleRow` / `ShowPreviewArt` paths).
- **Icon-only** — When **Icon** is the **only** selected field and the bitmap loads, the hover shows **Name** beside the 40 DIP icon (`ShowIconBesideGameNameRow` / `TryAppendGameArtRow` + `onlyIconSelected`); text uses `VerticalAlignment="Center"` next to the image.
- **Icons** — Inline MDL2 glyphs sit in a **32** DIP circular chip column with **10** DIP gap to text when `ShowFieldInlineIconsInHover` and the field is **not** game-art (`AppendTextDetailRow` / `AppendPlatformRow`). With icons off, body is full width — no reserved empty column in the preview.
- **Stat row** — When titles and inline icons are both on, the hover uses one grid row: chip | stacked label + value (`ConfigureFieldLabelTextBlock` + body). Preview uses `ShowStatRowLayout`; do not use a full-width title row above the chip for that mode.
- **Separators** — `AppendFieldBlockSeparator` / preview `ShowTopSeparator` + `SeparatorMargin` using `SeparatorPadDip` (0.5× block spacing). After a divider, preview must add the same **continuation top** as hover (`PreviewFieldTitleMargin` for title+value rows, `ContinuationRowOutermostMargin` on stat/chip/value-only/art roots) so space above and below the line both scale with `HoverFieldBlockSpacingDip`.
- **Settings** — Keep preview in sync with `HideFieldTitlesInHover`, `ShowFieldInlineIconsInHover`, `HoverFieldBlockSpacingDip`, and inner width relative to `HoverWidth` (**12** DIP horizontal padding on the preview border; hover `ChromePadding` **24**).

See **`src/GameHoverDetails/AGENTS.md`** (Preview vs hover parity) for the canonical checklist.
